      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not really. Logs will say:\ncreating instance x\ncreated instance x\n\nInstead of:\ncreating instance x\ninstance exists\n\nSince L139 doesn\u0027t log the 409 Conflict, from a logs reader\u0027s perspective it seems fine to me. When the instance actually got created is stored as the created timestamp anyway.\n\nL139 shouldn\u0027t really be happening regardless, since we use the same request ID each time, receiving a 409 Conflict means we sent a request to create a same-named instance so far after the initial request that GCE forgot the deduplication ID.\n\nIt\u0027s possible that it would be more reasonable to treat 409 as a hard failure (i.e. coincidentally generated a hostname that\u0027s already in use). Both cases seem extremely unlikely to me. I can\u0027t find a single instance of \"instance exists\" in GCE Provider logs.",
